#About Me:

I am a PhD candidate in my second year at Indiana University. My research focuses on finding abundances of odd, light elements (such as chlorine, phosphorus, and potassium) in stars using infrared spectroscopy. I attended the University of Minnesota for my undergraduate education. 

## Education:
* BS in Physics, University of Minnesota, 2014
* BS in Astrophysics, University of Minnesota, 2014
